<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1533,1999]" box="[199,344,1533,1559]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1533,1559]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1533,1999]" box="[199,400,1573,1599]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1573,1599]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1533,1999]" box="[199,992,1613,1639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,290,1613,1639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Female</emphasis>
(
<materialsCitation box="[305,992,1613,1639]" country="Brazil" location="Parque Estadual do Turvo" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
based on 
<typeStatus box="[418,521,1613,1639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B32614484329266F9853B198424691:8EC5C1D9484329266D5F556B9F904739" box="[592,899,1613,1639]" country="Brazil" name="Parque Estadual do Turvo" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Parque Estadual do Turvo</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[910,983,1613,1639]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1533,1999]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Carapace yellow, with a median white spot and a median stripe of dark setae. Anterior eye row procurved, lateral eyes approximately twice the diameter of median eyes. Posterior eyes of similar size, slightly larger than anterior lateral eyes. Clypeus, chelicerae and endites yellow. Labium orange, sternum and pedipalpi white. Legs yellow, with dark spots at the base of spines. Femur, patella, tibia and metatarsus with apical dark rings. Opisthosoma gray, dorsally covered with white guanine spots (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1116,1813,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 10" captionStartId="22.[151,269,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[304,1267,586,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-316@22.[294,1294,555,1405]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 10A–C. Architis turvo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female epigynum, ventral view; C, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097203/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets orange. Total length 4.6; carapace 1.8 long, 1.6 wide. Tibia I length 2.1, II 2.0, III 1.6, IV 1.7. Opisthosoma 2.5 long, 1.5 wide. CD encapsulated in rounded cases; fertilisation ducts emerging dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1187,1893,1919]" captionStart="FIGURES 10" captionStartId="22.[151,269,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[304,1267,586,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-316@22.[294,1294,555,1405]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 10A–C. Architis turvo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female epigynum, ventral view; C, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097203/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1533,1999]" box="[199,1436,1933,1959]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,1933,1959]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Natural history.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[457,507,1933,1959]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected by beating on understorey vegetation during the day.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
